title: Coachspeak: Eric Kessler, Humphrey St. Francis
text: Coachspeak: Eric Kessler, Humphrey St. Francis Bob Jensen HuskerlandPreps.com Publisher Talk about it in Football After last week rubbing out a challenge from unbeaten Osceola, and taking firm command of its district race, Humphrey St. Frnacis has improved to 5-1 on the season going into tonight's home game against 3-3 Elkhorn Valley.The preseason No. 1-ranked team in Class D-2, the Flyers were upset by still unbeaten CWC back in Week 4 but since then they've responded with three straight wins, beating those opponents by a combined 166-16.Earlier in the week I had a chance to talk with St. Francis head coach Eric Kessler , one of the more accomplished coaches in our state, having won state titles in both in football and boys basketball, and here is our conversation... FEATURED PRODUCT
